<h2>Create and manage accessibility issues</h2>

<p>Accessibility issues track defects, compliance gaps, and usability problems that need to be addressed to meet accessibility standards.</p>

<h3>Access requirements</h3>
<p>Only users with <strong>Super Admin</strong> or <strong>Admin</strong> roles can create and manage accessibility issues.</p>

<h3>Creating an accessibility issue</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Apps → Accessibility Issues and Statements</strong></li>
    <li>Select an enrolled product from the list</li>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Issues</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Add Issue</strong></li>
    <li>Fill in the issue details:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Issue Type:</strong> WCAG, Best Practice, or Usability</li>
            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Clear, descriptive title (required for Best Practice and Usability issues)</li>
            <li><strong>WCAG Criteria:</strong> Link to specific WCAG criteria (for WCAG issues)</li>
            <li><strong>Identified Date:</strong> When the issue was discovered</li>
            <li><strong>Identified Via:</strong> How it was found (Audit, Testing, Feedback, Complaint, GDS)</li>
            <li><strong>Description:</strong> Detailed description of the issue</li>
            <li><strong>Is Resolving:</strong> Whether remediation is planned</li>
            <li><strong>Planned Resolution Date:</strong> Target fix date (if resolving)</li>
            <li><strong>Non-Resolution Reason:</strong> Justification if not fixing (if not resolving)</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click <strong>Create Issue</strong></li>
</ol>

<h3>Issue lifecycle</h3>
<p>Issues progress through the following statuses:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Open:</strong> Newly created issue</li>
    <li><strong>In Progress:</strong> Work has begun on remediation</li>
    <li><strong>Resolved:</strong> Issue has been fixed and verified</li>
    <li><strong>Won't Fix:</strong> Decision made not to fix (requires justification)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Managing issues</h3>
<p>For each issue, you can:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Add comments:</strong> Provide updates, context, or notes</li>
    <li><strong>Update status:</strong> Move through the lifecycle</li>
    <li><strong>Link WCAG criteria:</strong> Associate with specific WCAG requirements</li>
    <li><strong>Set resolution dates:</strong> Track planned and actual resolution dates</li>
    <li><strong>Add resolution notes:</strong> Document how the issue was fixed</li>
    <li><strong>Request retest:</strong> Create retest requests for verification</li>
    <li><strong>View history:</strong> See all changes and updates</li>
</ul>

<h3>Best practices</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Be specific in issue descriptions - include steps to reproduce</li>
    <li>Link to relevant WCAG criteria for compliance tracking</li>
    <li>Set realistic resolution dates and update them if schedules change</li>
    <li>Document resolution steps for future reference</li>
    <li>Use comments to keep stakeholders informed of progress</li>
    <li>Provide clear justification for issues that won't be fixed</li>
</ul>

<h3>Viewing all issues</h3>
<p>You can view all accessibility issues across all products by:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Navigating to <strong>Apps → Accessibility Issues and Statements</strong></li>
    <li>Clicking on the <strong>All Issues</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Using filters to find specific issues</li>
</ol>

